Program: Omnibus
Title: From the Front Line
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376k99
Last Broadcast Date: 05 March 1992
'I could not tell lies or make things pleasant'. A look at the role of the news correspondent, from W.H. Russell reporting for the Times newspaper on the Crimean War onwards. Contributers include Philip Knightley, John Pilger and Max Hastings.